lowers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/saket/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "content_type": "application/vnd.android.package-archive", "state": "uploaded", "size": 6282718, "download_count": 101, "created_at": "2021-04-01T06:16:48Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-01T06:17:01Z", "browser_download_url": "https://github.com/saket/InboxRecyclerView/releases/download/v3.0/InboxRecyclerView_v3.0.0_sample.apk"}], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/saket/InboxRecyclerView/tarball/v3.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/saket/InboxRecyclerView/zipball/v3.0", "body": "### Nested Scrolling\r\nAs the highlight of this release, `InboxRecyclerView` now supports nested scrolling! Manual interception of pull-to-collapse gestures for scrollable content is no longer needed as long as your app uses nested-scrolling aware widgets such as `NestedScrollView`, `RecyclerView`, etc.\r\n\r\n### InboxItemExpander\r\nIf you aren\u2019t a fan of using adapter IDs for expanding list items because it\u2019s not 2020 anymore, `InboxRecyclerView`  now lets you supply any `Parcelable` type using a custom [InboxItemExpander](https://github.com/saket/InboxRecyclerView/blob/master/inboxrecyclerview/src/main/java/me/saket/inboxrecyclerview/expander/InboxItemExpander.kt). You can read more about it here: [Custom expansion keys](https://github.com/saket/InboxRecyclerView/wiki/Custom-expansion-keys).\r\n\r\n### Haptic feedback\r\nThis release introduces `PageCollapseEligibilityHapticFeedback` that can play haptic feedback during a pull-to-collapse gesture to indicate when the page can be released to collapse.\r\n\r\n### Breaking changes\r\nFor apps that use a custom `DimPainter`, this release unfortunately introduces a breaking change to the function signature of `DimPainter#cancelAnimation()`.\r\n"}
